PROJECT NAME:

nodejs-mongodb-rest-api-practice

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT SUMMARY:

Practice-based learning project for understanding MongoDB integration with Node.js
and Express.js using a clean, concept-wise folder structure.

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT DESCRIPTION:

This is a Node.js and Express.js practice project created to learn MongoDB
integration step by step.
Each MongoDB-related concept is organized in a separate folder with its own
app.js file.
Only one concept is executed at a time by importing it in index.js.
This approach helps in learning database operations clearly without mixing
multiple concepts in a single file.

--------------------------------------------------

CONCEPTS COVERED:

- Connect MongoDB with NodeJS
- Display data from MongoDB on UI using EJS
- Create API with MongoDB and Node.js
- Save data using POST Form
- Save data using POST REST API
- Delete data using REST API
- Populate, Fetch, Update & Delete data with MongoDB

--------------------------------------------------

CONCEPT FOLDER MAPPING:

Connect MongoDB						        -> 01-connect-mongodb/app.js

Display Data on UI (EJS)					-> 02-display-ui-ejs/app.js

Create API with MongoDB					    -> 03-make-api/app.js

Save Data using POST Form				    -> 04-post-form-save/app.js

Save Data using POST REST API			    -> 05-post-rest-api/app.js

Delete Data using REST API				    -> 06-delete-rest-api/app.js

Populate, Fetch, Update & Delete (CRUD)		-> 07-populate-crud-mongodb/app.js

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT STRUCTURE NOTE:
- Each concept has its own folder
- Each folder contains a single app.js file
- Only ONE concept should run at a time
- index.js acts as the concept runner

--------------------------------------------------

NODE_MODULES NOTE:
The node_modules folder contains all required dependencies for this project.
This folder is not included in the GitHub repository.
It is generated automatically after installing packages.

Command to install node_modules:
npm install

--------------------------------------------------

REQUIRED PACKAGES & COMMANDS:

1) Express.js
Used to create server, routes, and handle HTTP requests.
Command:
npm install express

2) MongoDB (Official Driver)
Used to connect Node.js with MongoDB database and perform CRUD operations.
Command:
npm install mongodb

3) EJS (Template Engine)
Used to display MongoDB data dynamically on the UI.
Command:
npm install ejs

4) Nodemon (Development Dependency)
Used to automatically restart the server on file changes.
Command:
npm install nodemon --save-dev

Install all packages together:
npm install express mongodb ejs
npm install nodemon --save-dev

--------------------------------------------------

HOW TO RUN THE PROJECT:

Run with Node.js:
node index.js

Run with Nodemon (Recommended):
npx nodemon index.js

--------------------------------------------------

IMPORTANT NOTES:
- Only ONE app.js file should be active at a time
- Uncomment the required concept import in index.js
- Keep all other imports commented to avoid port conflicts
- MongoDB must be running before starting the project
- Field names in MongoDB should be consistent for proper UI display

--------------------------------------------------

TECHNOLOGIES USED:
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- EJS
- JavaScript (ES Modules)

--------------------------------------------------

PROJECT PURPOSE:
- Learn MongoDB integration with Node.js
- Understand REST APIs with database operations
- Practice CRUD operations using real database
- Build strong backend fundamentals
- Maintain a clean, modular, and revision-friendly structure
- Prepare for real-world backend and MERN stack projects

--------------------------------------------------
